  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2001-06-14", 
    "text": "Consumer Energy Commission Act of 2001 - Establishes the Consumer Energy Commission to study and report to Congress on significant price spikes in the following energy products during the ten years preceding the date of this Act: (1) electricity; (2) gasoline; (3) home heating oil; (4) natural gas; and (5) propane."
